---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import HowWeWork from '../components/HowWeWork.astro';
import ProductCard from '../components/ProductCard.astro';
import DoooooGlyph from '../components/DoooooGlyph.astro';
import TeamWorkflowDiagram from '../components/TeamWorkflowDiagram.astro';
import ProdectWorkflowDiagram from '../components/ProdectWorkflowDiagram.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout>
  <Nav />
  <Hero />
  <HowWeWork />

  <section id="products" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-10 pt-24 pb-12">
    <p class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="inline-block h-px w-8 bg-[var(--color-ink)]/30"></span>
      Three products
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[44px] leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.025em] font-medium max-w-xl">
      The tasks. The team that runs them. The plan that ties it together.
    </h2>
  </section>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-10">
    <ProductCard
      product="doooo-app"
      index="01"
      name="Doooo App"
      tagline="Tasks, the way you actually plan them. And the remote for your AI team."
    >
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 -mt-2">
        <DoooooGlyph class="text-[var(--color-brand)]" size={28} />
        <span class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--color-muted)]">iOS · Android · Web</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        A task manager that listens. Speak your todos, see your week, share lists with the people in your life.
        Mobile-first, syncs everywhere.
      </p>
      <p>
        Doooo App is also the <strong>remote control for Doooo Hub</strong>: assign work to one of your AI
        agents from your phone, watch the job run on your desktop, ship from the couch. Same surface, two kinds of
        teammate — the humans you actually know, and the agents you hired.
      </p>
      <p>
        Built using the Prodect workflow. The same surface where Prodect's human Subtasks land — clear, scoped, ready
        to do.
      </p>
    </ProductCard>

    <ProductCard
      product="doooo-hub"
      index="02"
      name="Doooo Hub"
      tagline="Hire a team. Or build your own. Or sell it."
    >
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 -mt-2">
        <DoooooGlyph class="text-[var(--color-brand)]" size={28} />
        <span class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--color-muted)]">macOS · Apple Silicon · MLX</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Doooo Hub isn't one assistant — it's a <strong>team of agents running a workflow together</strong>. Start
        with a built-in team from Doooo: <strong>Content Creator</strong> ships with a researcher, a copywriter, an
        editor, a social-media manager and four others, already wired to hand off to each other end-to-end. Brand
        Designer, Product Designer, and E-commerce Seller teams work the same way.
      </p>
      <p>
        Or build your own team from scratch — design your own agents, pick their tools, write the workflow that
        connects them (the workflow is part of the team). When it's good, <strong>publish it to the marketplace</strong>
        and let other people hire your team for their work.
      </p>

      <TeamWorkflowDiagram />

      <p>
        On macOS, Doooo Hub runs local models through <strong>Apple's MLX framework</strong> — the unified-memory,
        Apple-Silicon-native runtime that makes 7-70B-parameter models genuinely fast on a MacBook, no GPU rental
        required. Cloud LLMs work too, but the headline is on-device: your code, your keys, your repo, your hardware.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[14px]">
        Driven by Doooo App. Planned by Prodect.
      </p>
    </ProductCard>

    <ProductCard
      product="prodect"
      index="03"
      name="Prodect"
      tagline="Building itself, the way it'll build yours."
    >
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 -mt-2">
        <span class="font-mono text-[var(--color-brand)] font-semibold text-[16px]">{`{ }`}</span>
        <span class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--color-muted)]">Open core · GPL-3.0 + hosted brain</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Open-source Jira, with planning intelligence built in. Describe what you want to build; Prodect produces an
        <strong>Epic → Story → Subtask tree</strong>, routes each Subtask to the right executor — coding agent or
        human — and hands the coding ones a rich prompt your agent (Claude Code, Cursor, Devin, Aider) can execute
        end-to-end.
      </p>
      <p>
        The product isn't shipped yet. But the <em>workflow</em> is — and we're using it right now to build Prodect
        itself, plus Doooo App and Doooo Hub. Today a human plays the planner role by hand; soon Prodect's planner
        agent will play it automatically. Same workflow, different planner.
      </p>

      <ProdectWorkflowDiagram />

      <p>
        <strong>prodect-core</strong> is GPL-3.0 open-source — Work Items, Stories, dependency graphs, multi-tenant
        workspaces, the tree-view UI, GitHub integration. The planning brain (<strong>prodect-ai</strong>) ships as
        a hosted service. Browsers only ever talk to prodect-core; the AI layer is server-to-server. Same playbook
        GitLab, Sentry, Plane, and Mattermost use.
      </p>
    </ProductCard>
  </div>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-10 mt-24 pt-20 pb-8 border-t border-[var(--color-line)]/15">
    <p class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="inline-block h-px w-8 bg-[var(--color-ink)]/30"></span>
      Manifesto
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-7 md:col-start-2">
        <p class="text-[22px] md:text-[28px] leading-[1.4] tracking-[-0.015em] text-[var(--color-ink)]">
          moooon is a small studio in a quiet corner of the internet. We build tools we wished existed, ship them when
          they're ready, and keep them simple enough that one person can hold the whole thing in their head.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-[16px] leading-[1.65] text-[var(--color-muted)]">
          The loop above isn't a marketing diagram — it's literally how this site, Doooo App, Doooo Hub, and Prodect
          itself get built. No funding rounds, no growth-hacking, no roadmap theatre. Just three products and the work
          to make them good.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
